he most influential figures behind the New Romantic movement of the early 1980s.', 'Jonah Matranga | Jonah Rzadzinski Matranga (born Jonah Sonz Matranga, August 11, 1969, Brookline, Massachusetts) is a singer, songwriter, and guitarist who has released a variety of solo material under his own name and onelinedrawing, and has previously been part of the bands Far and New End Original (an anagram of "onelinedrawing") and Gratitude. He now continues to work and tour under onelinedrawing\'.', 'Strange Cruise | Strange Cruise was a short-lived 1980s British pop rock group, fronted by former Visage singer Steve Strange and Wendy Cruise (aka Wendy Wu, the former singer of The Photos). The band released only one, self-titled album in 1986.'], 'question': 'have Jonah Matranga and Steve Strange both been singers?', 'reasoning': 'Yes, both Jonah Matranga and Steve Strange have been singers. Steve Strange was a Welsh pop singer who became famous as the leader of the new wave synthpop group Visage, and Jonah Matranga is a singer, songwriter, and guitarist who has released a variety of solo material under his own name and the moniker onelinedrawing.', 'search_query': 'singers jonah matranga steve strange'}) (input_keys=None)]

